  "texts": [
    "Concerning Peak wrist elevation (mm), statistical analysis showed a significant Intention * Block interaction effect (χ 2 (7) = 163.66, p <.001), with the difference in peak wrist elevation between social and personal actions increasing progressively throughout the blocks of trials.",
    "Coherently, simple effects analysis showed that peak wrist elevation was not statistically different in social compared to personal actions in the baseline block 1 (Social -Personal estimate = 0.04, SE = 0.05, z.ratio = 0.81, p =.210), whereas it was in block 8 (Social -Personal estimate = 0.22, SE = 0.05, z.ratio = 4.23, p <.001).",
    "Post-hoc analysis showed that the difference in peak wrist elevation between social and personal actions started to be significantly different from the baseline block 1 from block 2 on (see Fig. 4.A).",
    "Concerning Peak wrist velocity (mm.s -1), statistical analysis showed a significant Intention * Block interaction effect (F (7,2830.21) = 2.16, p =.035), with the difference in peak wrist velocity between social and personal actions changing throughout blocks of trials.",
    "Nevertheless, simple effects analysis showed that peak wrist velocity was not statistically different in social compared to personal actions interaction effect (F (7,2833.08) = 0.59, p =.761), with the difference in percentage of deceleration time between social and personal actions not changing across the blocks of trials."
